<li id="cite_note-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book">Foltz, Richard (2013). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=sZRGAQAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA95&amp;lpg=PA95&amp;dq=buddhist+viharas+found+in+modern+day+iran&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=6fa8kamUbK&amp;sig=TrrlAWcGC-OtT9yWpqHTrnfrPG0&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjxxY-w8ZPYAhUOw2MKHbBkCpIQ6AEIdDAQ#v=onepage&amp;q=buddhist%20viharas%20found%20in%20modern%20day%20iran&amp;f=false"><i>Religions of Iran:From Prehistory to the Present</i></a>. p.&#160;95<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2017-12-18</span></span>. <q>In the centuries before the Arab conquests Buddhism was spread throughout the eastern Iranian world. Buddhist sites have been found in Afghanistan, Turkmenistan, Uzbekistan, and Tajikistan, as well as within Iran itself.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Religions+of+Iran%3AFrom+Prehistory+to+the+Present&amp;rft.pages=95&amp;rft.date=2013&amp;rft.aulast=Foltz&amp;rft.aufirst=Richard&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DsZRGAQAAQBAJ%26pg%3DPA95%26lpg%3DPA95%26dq%3Dbuddhist%2Bviharas%2Bfound%2Bin%2Bmodern%2Bday%2Biran%26source%3Dbl%26ots%3D6fa8kamUbK%26sig%3DTrrlAWcGC-OtT9yWpqHTrnfrPG0%26hl%3Den%26sa%3DX%26ved%3D0ahUKEwjxxY-w8ZPYAhUOw2MKHbBkCpIQ6AEIdDAQ%23v%3Donepage%26q%3Dbuddhist%2520viharas%2520found%2520in%2520modern%2520day%2520iran%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMahayana" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Nattier,_Jan_2003_p._174-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Nattier,_Jan_2003_p._174_8-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nattier,_Jan_2003_p._174_8-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Nattier, Jan (2003), <i>A few good men: the Bodhisattva path according to the Inquiry of Ugra</i>: p. 174</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Nattier, Jan (2003), <i>A few good men: the Bodhisattva path according to the Inquiry of Ugra</i>: p. 172</span></li>
